Job Description:
The Federal Home Loan Bank of San Francisco (“Bank”) is a cooperative, wholesale bank that provides liquidity to its members and helps meet community credit needs by providing credit products and services to member financial institutions through all phases of the economic cycle. The Bank’s members include commercial banks, credit unions, industrial loan companies, savings institutions, insurance companies, and community development financial institutions headquartered in Arizona, California, and Nevada. The Bank is member focused; embraces accountability to meet commitments and uphold our governance, risk, and control standards as a government sponsored enterprise; and values differences to foster an inclusive culture.
As a Data Governance AD, you will join the Data Science Enterprise Risk Management (“ERM”) team that is responsible for data governance/management and introducing data automation initiatives that increase overall efficiencies and drives faster data and risk-based decision-making across the Bank. This role is expected to direct, plan, and oversee delivery of deeper data analysis to others at the Bank. Additionally, this position is intended to leverage data-driven insights and advanced data techniques to support the mission of the bank and bolster the identification, assessment, monitoring, management, and reporting of risks.
Success in this role entails knowledge of general data analytics techniques, along with broad expertise in data governance and operational risk management. This role is at the intersection of leadership, business support, and engagement that will span across teams and business units. This role is expected to have a significant impact in supporting the Bank’s mission through data-powered products, streamlined processes, analytics services, and Bank policies.
Key Accountabilities:
Actively drive, populate, and support enablement of the Bank’s data catalog which consists of enterprise data domains, sub-domains, models, measures, attributes, and data services at the Bank;
Enhance and scale the Banks’s data processing infrastructure, utilizing innovative frameworks to drive efficiency and promote automation to support data and analytics activities across the Bank;
Define, develop, and document procedures for increasing data availability and quality while promoting responsible data usage and access controls;
Participate in the definition and design of Bank’s domain services and taxonomies, working directly with our data owners and data expert teams;
Partner with Security teams and iterate on privacy-related guidelines and procedures to mitigate data leakage and privacy risk;
Collaborate utilize modern data management best practices for data storage, ETLs, and data cleaning of structured and unstructured data and proactively identify and solution data quality issues.
Lead outreach efforts to showcase and share core capabilities, leading data analytics practices, key insights, and modernization opportunities;
Resolve data problems through in-depth evaluation of business processes, system processes, enterprise policies and procedures;
Document potential business risk and escalate it to leadership for consideration;
Assist the ERM team with strategy-implementation and improvement opportunities;
Identify and drive areas for quick wins in the near term, while keeping an eye on how those wins fit into an overall long-term data infrastructure and analytics activities strategy;
Write and present clear and concise reports/presentations containing meaningful observations and recommendations/conclusions, to present analysis findings to business stakeholders; And document procedures performed;
Assist in preparing monthly enterprise risk reporting and in the presentation of materials to the ERC.
Critical Competencies:
5+ years of work experience in data governance and management leadership, and data-related professional experiences (e.g., data lakes and data warehousing, data management, cloud data architectures, data research, data analysis, etc.)
3+ years of in the Banking industry, experience in credit/collateral risk and market risk a plus.
Strong expertise in modern domain design principles, analytical dimensional modeling best practices, and data modeling approaches for modern software development
Multiple experiences in helping organizations put in place effective data governance, data management, and data stewardship/data integrity processes that drive results;
Strong knowledge of data governance frameworks and compliance standards; a certification in one or more data management disciplines a plus (MDM, CDMP, DGSP, GDPR, PII, etc.);
Experience in data architecture, data manipulation, cleansing, and transformation leading to a cohesive data strategy;
Experience in developing cloud ETL and date pipeline with various technologies such as Python, AWS Sagemaker, Airflow, Talend, AWS Lambda, MongoDB, Jenkins, and AWS Dynamo;
Hands-on data processing and database data modeling experience and strong level understanding of ETL fundamentals and building and maintaining efficient data pipelines;
Demonstrated ability to identify business and technical impacts of user requirements and incorporate them into the project schedule;
Experience with modern software delivery practices, including source control, testing, production implementation, and continuous delivery using API, Python, SQL and AWS services; and ability to write code independently;
Excellent organization and project management skills and able to work independently;
Ability to organize, prioritize, and complete multiple tasks in a high paced environment;
Must have excellent interpersonal skills to work in a team environment and to influence and interface with a broad range of stakeholders at all levels, both internal and external; and
Able to communicate complex analytical insights in a simple, concise manner, and to build strong relationships with various business units to effectively convert insights into action.
SALARY RANGE: $155K - $170K
